# Go Backend — MANDATORY: masterfabric-go architecture

The hackathon ruleset REQUIRES using the architecture of
https://github.com/gurkanfikretgunak/masterfabric-go as the backend infrastructure.
Building a custom/own backend architecture is NOT accepted (disqualification risk).

## How we use it
- The masterfabric-go repository is vendored into `services/api/` and is the backend base.
- Keep its upstream `LICENSE` (AGPL v3.0) inside `services/api/`; credit it in the root README.
- Do NOT rewrite its architecture. EXTEND it: add our feature as a new bounded context.

## Architecture (do not deviate)
- Clean / hexagonal architecture, Domain-Driven Design with bounded contexts.
- Layers: `internal/domain` (zero external deps) → `internal/application` (use cases + DTOs)
  → `internal/infrastructure` (postgres/redis/http impls). Entry point: `cmd/server`.
- Stack: Go 1.22+, Chi router, PostgreSQL (pgx), Redis, goose migrations, JWT (golang-jwt) + bcrypt,
  slog (structured JSON), go-playground/validator, OpenTelemetry/Prometheus.
- Kafka is OPTIONAL: run with `KAFKA_ENABLED=false` (in-process EventBus) for the hackathon/Render.
- Health probes `/health/live` `/health/ready`, `/metrics`. Server on :8080.

## Our feature (Kaldırım Skoru) inside this architecture
- Add a new bounded context, e.g. `internal/domain/walkability` (entities: ScoreRequest, Detection,
  StreetScore, Grade) with repository interfaces.
- `internal/application/walkability`: use cases — ScoreStreet, ScorePhoto — orchestrating
  Google Street View fetch + Python CV sidecar (`/anonymize` then `/detect`) + scoring formula.
- `internal/infrastructure`: Street View HTTP client (HMAC-SHA1 sign ONLY if a signing secret is set,
  else call unsigned), sidecar HTTP client (uses `INTERNAL_SIDECAR_TOKEN`), Roboflow proxy if needed.
- Expose endpoints under the project's `/api/v1` convention (e.g. `POST /api/v1/score`,
  `POST /api/v1/score/photo`). Reuse its middleware, error envelopes, validator, slog.
- Scoring weights/caps live in `scoring.config.json`, loaded at startup (editable without code changes).

## Hard rules (unchanged)
- Secrets read from env at startup; FAIL FAST if missing. Never hardcode keys.
- Raw image bytes: `bytes.NewReader` only, in-memory, `defer Body.Close()`. No temp files, no logging raw bytes.
- Log `{face_count, plate_count, image_sha256}` before any detector call. Anonymization runs first.
- Resize images > 5 MB to ≤ 1280×1280 before Roboflow (5 MB ingest cap).
